        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-17T13:19:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "One thing we\u0027ve been wanting for other APIs is the ability to specify a buffer that the output can be copied into. This way, we don\u0027t have to do as much explicit copying into a WASM heap.\n\nProposed solution: Add a field to TextPropertiesRequests (TextPropertiesOptions?) called output or outputBuffer. If provided, this function will put the data into that buffer (throwing an exception if the buffer is too small) and return a reference to the buffer.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 70,
        "startChar": 39,
        "endLine": 70,
        "endChar": 50
      },
      "revId": "71c2789454b6b8954491b0944d490d44b359a41a",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
