      "writtenOn": "2021-06-17T13:19:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This psuedocode was a bit hard for me to understand at first. What about trying to keep it as valid TS/JS code?\n\n  let mask \u003d TextPropertiesMasks.IsWhiteSpace | TextPropertiesMasks.SoftLineBreak;\n  const spacesAndBreakIndices \u003d [];\n  results.forEach((props, idx) \u003d\u003e {\n    if ((props \u0026 mask) \u003e 0) {\n      spacesAndBreakIndices.push(idx);\n    }\n  });\n  // spacesAndBreakIndices at this point should be [7,9,15,19,24,28,37,44,52,65] because\n  // the code points at those indexes were spaces and could be treated as soft line breaks.\n\n  mask \u003d TextPropertiesMasks.HardLineBreak;\n  const hardBreakIndices \u003d [];\n  results.forEach((props, idx) \u003d\u003e {\n    if ((props \u0026 mask) \u003e 0) {\n      hardBreakIndices.push(idx);\n    }\n  });\n  // hardBreakIndices at this point should be [34], because that is the only index\n  // which is a hard break in this text (\\n).\n\n  // Possible example with surrogate pairs.",
